Date: 10 Oct 2000 12:26:11 -0400 (EDT)
From: Meredith Golden <mgolden@ciesin.org>

Human Morbidity? Request for Information
----------------------------------------
I have not seen many references to long-term health effects for humans
infected by the West Nile virus. Are there any studies monitoring the
health of those infected in the New York metropolitan area during the 1999
outbreak? Recently, I saw a quote by Dr. Paul Epstein in the Ottawa Citizen
that stated, "Of the 62 survivors [of West Nile Virus infection, most are
suffering from neurological disabilities." It seems that morbidity, rather
than mortality, from West Nile virus infection could be the key public
health problem. I would be interested in knowing of any studies or
individuals focusing on this dimension of the problem.
--
Meredith Golden
CIESIN at Columbia University
Geosciences/LDEO PO Box 1000,
61 Route 9W Palisades NY 10964
<mgolden@ciesin.columbia.edu>
